The paper deals with the problem of single image inverse, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also heavily relies on deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper proposes a stopping criterion based on measuring the orthogonality between signal and noise, which could be related to information theory (cs.IT) or neural engineering (cs.NE).
